lemma noHo_exp_and_known_needs_many_calls (S : List (Call n))
    (S_noHo : noHo S)
    (k : Fin n)
    (h : isExpert (after n S) k)
    (h2 : allKnow (after n S) k)
    : 2 * n - 2 - v S k ≤ S.length := by
  -- This follows from Lemma 6 in Baker and Shostak (1972).
  -- Let S_k be the calls in S involving k, so |S_k| = v S k.
  -- Every agent j ≠ k must have their secret reach k and also learn k's secret.
  -- In a noHo sequence, each agent j not in S_k requires at least two calls
  -- in S \ S_k to both send their secret and receive k's secret.
  -- If j is in S_k, it requires fewer calls in S \ S_k.
  -- Summing these requirements leads to S.length ≥ 2 * (n - 1) - v S k.
  sorry
```
