  have : 2 * n - 2 ≤ S.length + v S k := by
    -- Based on Lemma 6 in Baker and Shostak (1972).
    -- In a noHo sequence, any call not involving agent k can either move a secret
    -- toward agent k or move k's secret toward another agent, but not both.
    -- Otherwise, k would hear their own secret, violating the noHo condition.
    -- Since there are n-1 other secrets and n-1 other agents, we need 2(n-1)
    -- total transmissions, which only overlap in calls involving k.
    sorry
  omega
```
